OL,3,CLabour and Conservatives rule out
OL,4,Craising VAT after General Election
OL,6,FWriting in the Telegraph, Mr Hunt said
OL,7,Fthat a Conservative government would
OL,8,Fnot increase income tax, national
OL,9,Finsurance and VAT throughout the next
OL,10,FParliament.
OL,12,FClaims that were rubbished by Labour
OL,13,FShadow Chancellor Rachel Reeves, who
OL,14,Fpointed to her parties' claims that
OL,15,Fthe Tories are staring down a #71
OL,16,Fbillion blackhole with no plans to
OL,17,Ffill it.
OL,19,FReeves, however, also denied that her
OL,20,Fparty had any plans to uprate tax,
OL,21,Fnational insurance or VAT.
